// `timenow` is the current UTC time in milliseconds. It is wall-clock, so it
// can only be asserted relatively: it must sit past a fixed date in the past.
log.info(str.tostring(timenow > timestamp(2024, 1, 1, 0, 0)))

// Unlike `time`, which is the bar's own opening timestamp, `timenow` is not
// bar data — the fixture's bars are timestamped near the epoch.
log.info(str.tostring(timenow > time))

// Expected output:
// true
// true
